{"title_page": "Jackson Robert Scott", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jackson Robert Scott\n| image              = Jackson Robert Scott MTV 2018.png\n| caption            = Scott in 2018\n| birth_name         = Jackson Robert Scott\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2008|9|18}}\n| birth_place        = [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2015-present\n}}\n\n'''Jackson Robert Scott''' (born September 18, 2008)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2017/09/07/it-movie-georgie-actor-remake-interview/|title=\u2018It\u2019 Star Jackson Robert Scott, 8, Reveals Why He Wasn\u2019t Scared At All Of Pennywise & More|last=Thompson|first=Avery|date=2017-09-07|website=HollywoodLife|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> is an American child actor known for playing [[Georgie Denbrough]] in the films ''[[It (2017 film)|It Chapter One]]'' (2017) and ''[[It Chapter Two]]'' (2019) and Bode Locke in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]'' (2020-).\n\n== Early Life ==\nScott was born and raised in [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]].<ref name=\"AZFamily.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.azfamily.com/archives/it-has-valley-connection/article_eb4d88d0-08ce-5bb2-ac0f-0424c7817539.html|title='It' has Valley connection|last=Reporter|first=Maria Hechanova|website=AZFamily|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/entertainment/movies/2020/03/23/jackson-robert-scott-arizona-born-actor-locke-key-netflix-stephen-kings-it/4939992002/|title=You might know this Arizona-born actor as Georgie in 'It.' Now he's in a new Netflix show|last=Ludden|first=Nicole|website=azcentral|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He is enrolled in his school's Mandarin Immersion Program, in which he learns to speak [[Mandarin Chinese]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Jackson Robert Scott at the \"IT\" premiere on FabulousTV|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8httfWqfcPE|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> He is also a [[Boy Scouts of America|boy scout]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Begj9RPFaDB/|title=Jackson Robert Scott\u2019s Instagram photo: \u201cHaving fun at the Cub Scout Pinewood Derby Race... A 65 year old tradition! \ud83c\udfce\ud83d\udea6\ud83c\udfc1 #cubscouts #cubscoutsofamerica #pinewoodderby\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bf4wO__FXYZ/|title=Jackson Robert Scott on Instagram: \u201cCrossed the bridge...I\u2019m now officially a Webelo! \ud83d\ude01\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8DT94DlzFD/|title=Jackson Robert Scott on Instagram: \u201cMy 5th Pinewood Derby Race! \ud83c\udfce\ud83c\udfc1Such a fun day with my Cub Scout/Arrow of Light troop! #cubscouts #pinewoodderby #boyscoutsofamerica\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nHe was a part of the CGTV acting program, where he learned many of his acting techniques. While at the CGTV program, he worked with actors from [[Nickelodeon]] and [[Disney]], as well as [[Adrian R'Mante]], the founder of CGTV.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/celebrating-silver-screen-debut-cgtv-graduate/|title=Celebrating the Silver Screen Debut of a CGTV Graduate|last=R'Mante|date=2017-09-06|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> His favorite class was Improvisational Workshop.<ref name=\"Jackson Robert Scott Hits Prime Time TV\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/cgtv-alum-jackson-robert-scott-hits-prime-time-tv-hollywood/|title=Jackson Robert Scott Hits Prime Time TV|last=R'Mante|date=2016-12-29|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nHe was discovered by a top agency some time after his time with CGTV and began his start in auditioning and self-taping for top-tier television shows.<ref name=\"5 Year gets 15 agent callbacks and secures a costar role in Criminal Minds after CGTV\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/criminal-minds-after-cgtv/|title=5 Year gets 15 agent callbacks|last=R'Mante|date=2016-07-27|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nScott got his breakout role in 2015 on ''[[Criminal Minds]]'', a prime time American TV series. Scott was cast in [[Criminal_Minds_(season_11)|Season 11]]\u2019s fourth episode, titled \"Outlaw\", as Cole Vasquez. The episode aired on October 21, 2015.<ref name=\"Criminal Minds 11x04 IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=Outlaw|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt4920092/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> He also played a minor character in an episode of ''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]'' titled \"[[TEOTWAWKI_(Fear_the_Walking_Dead)|TEOTWAWKI]]\", playing the child version of the character Troy Otto.<ref name=\"Fear The Walking Dead 3x03 IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=TEOTWAWKI|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt6082752/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Scott was cast to play [[Georgie Denbrough]] in the [[It_(2017_film)|2017 film adaptation]] of [[Stephen King|Stephen King's]] novel [[It (novel)|''It'']].<ref name=\":0\" /> Georgie is a character that [[It (character)|Pennywise the Dancing Clown]] haunts at the start of the film. Scott had said that he did not feel intimidated or scared of [[Bill Skarsg\u00e5rd]], who played Pennywise, as Skarsg\u00e5rd was a nice person in real life.<ref name=\"Video Interview of Jackson at the premiere of IT in 2017\">{{Citation|title=\ud83c\udf6d Jackson Robert Scott co-stars with Bill Skarsg\u00e5rd (Pennywise) & describes him with & no makeup|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qmKLb1KczPI|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Scott attended the premiere for the film at [[Grauman's Chinese Theatre]].<ref name=\"Another Jackson Interview at the IT premiere\">{{Citation|title=Jackson Robert Scott (Georgie) - \"IT\" Premiere 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bkAhne1Xk6I|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> He reprised his role of Georgie in the sequel, ''[[It Chapter Two]]'', which was released on September 6, 2019.<ref name=\"IT: Chapter Two IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=It: Chapter Two|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt7349950/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nScott was cast in the role of Troy for the short film [[Skin_(2018_short_film)|''Skin'']] (2018), directed by Guy Nattiv, which would go on to win the [[Academy Award for Best Live Action Short Film]] at the [[91st Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Skin Oscar Page\">{{Cite web|title=Skin: Short Film (Live Action) Oscar Nominees 2019|url=https://oscar.go.com/nominees/short-film-live-action/skin|website=oscar.go.com|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Skin Wins Oscar\">{{Citation|title=\"Skin\" wins Best Live Action Short Film|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x-fsRO3CbW8|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nContinuing in the horror genre, Scott played the title role of Miles Blume in the 2019 film [[The Prodigy (film)|''The Prodigy'']], directed by [[Nicholas_McCarthy_(director)|Nicholas McCarthy]]. This marked his first starring role in a feature film, and he co-starred alongside [[Taylor Schilling]].<ref name=\"Jackson cast in The Prodigy article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/jackson-robert-scott-horror-movie-taylor-schilling-nicholas-mccarthy-midnight-meat-train-1202308536/|title=Jackson Robert Scott Joins Orion\u2019s Horror Pic From Nicholas McCarthy|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|date=2018-03-02|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"The Prodigy Trailer\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/the-prodigy-trailer-taylor-schilling-jackson-robert-scott-1202529056/|title=\u2018The Prodigy\u2019 Trailer: Taylor Schilling Tries To Make Sense Of Her Young Son\u2019s Strange Behavior|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|date=2019-01-04|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n[[Andr\u00e9s Muschietti]] had recruited Scott to be a part of his one-hour series pilot of ''[[Locke & Key]]'' for [[Hulu]] as one of the leading young actors opposite [[Frances O'Connor]]. He played the part of Bode Locke, the youngest of the siblings.<ref name=\"Jackson Hulu L&K Pilot Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/locke-key-it-jackson-robert-scott-cast-hulu-pilot-1202157390/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019: Young \u2018It\u2019 Co-Star To Play Bode Locke In Hulu Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2017-08-29|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Hulu passed on the pilot and declined to order it to series.<ref name=\"Hulu passed over Locke & Key series Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/locke-key-pilot-dead-not-going-to-series-hulu-pauses-pilot-orders-shopped-1202354352/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019 Not Going To Series At Hulu As Streamer Pauses Pilot Orders|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2018-03-27|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> However, [[Netflix]] later redeveloped the [[Locke & Key (TV series)|series]] with a new cast, only keeping Scott as Bode from the Hulu cast.<ref name=\"Netflix orders Locke & Key to series Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/locke-key-drama-carlton-cuse-joe-hill-series-order-netflix-aron-eli-coleite-meredith-averill-1202433692/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019 Drama From Carlton Cuse & Joe Hill Gets Series Order At Netflix, Aron Eli Coleite & Meredith Averill Join As EPs|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2018-07-25|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> The first season was released on Netflix on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/locke-key-gets-netflix-premiere-date-1259502|title='Locke & Key' Gets Netflix Premiere Date, Ending 9-Year Journey to Screen|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref> Scott stated in an interview for [[The Arizona Republic|AZCentral]] that Bode has been his favorite character to play, because he shares a lot of qualities with that character, such as his fun-loving personality and his love of bacon. The writers of the show met Jackson while filming so they could incorporate aspects from his real life personality into the character of Bode. Scott also said in the same interview that he grew very close to the other actors of ''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]'' while they were filming the show.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2018, Scott was cast in the role of Tate Millikin for the upcoming independent film ''Gossamer Folds,'' directed by Lisa Donato. He co-stars with [[Alexandra Grey]] and [[Shane West]]. The film is produced by [[Yeardley Smith]].<ref name=\"Gossamer Folds Annoucement Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/yeardley-smiths-paperclip-ltd-gossamer-folds-alexandra-grey-lisa-donato-lgbtq-diversity-inclusion-1202502237/|title=Yeardley Smith\u2019s Paperclip Ltd. Sets Transgender Drama \u2018Gossamer Folds\u2019 Starring \u2018Transparent\u2019s Alexandra Grey|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|last2=Ramos|first2=Dino-Ray|date=2018-11-15|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[It (2017 film)|It]]''\n|[[Georgie Denbrough]]\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Skin (2018 short film)|Skin]]''\n|Troy\n|Academy Award for Best Live Action Short Film\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Prodigy (film)|The Prodigy]]''\n|Miles Blume\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[It Chapter Two]]''\n|Georgie Denbrough\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''Gossamer Folds''\n|Tate Millikin\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''Rising''\n|Luke\n|Post-production, short film<ref name=\"Rising (2020) IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=Rising (2020)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11093922/|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Criminal Minds]]''\n|Cole Vasquez\n|Episode: \"Outlaw\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]''\n|Young Troy Otto\n|Episode: \"[[TEOTWAWKI (Fear the Walking Dead)|TEOTWAWKI]]\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]''\n|Bode Locke\n|Main role\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [[imdbname:7669135|Jackson Robert Scott]] on [[IMDb]]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/jacksonrobertscottofficial/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Instagram]]\n*[https://twitter.com/jacksonrscottit/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Twitter]]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/JacksonRobertScottOfficial/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Facebook]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scott, Jackson Robert}}\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:2008 births]]\n[[Category:People from Arizona]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jackson Robert Scott\n| image              = Jackson Robert Scott MTV 2018.png\n| caption            = Scott in 2018\n| birth_name         = Jackson Robert Scott\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2008|9|18}}\n| birth_place        = [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2015-present\n}}\n\n'''Jackson Robert Scott''' (born September 18, 2008)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2017/09/07/it-movie-georgie-actor-remake-interview/|title=\u2018It\u2019 Star Jackson Robert Scott, 8, Reveals Why He Wasn\u2019t Scared At All Of Pennywise & More|last=Thompson|first=Avery|date=2017-09-07|website=HollywoodLife|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> is an American child actor known for playing [[Georgie Denbrough]] in the films ''[[It (2017 film)|It Chapter One]]'' (2017) and ''[[It Chapter Two]]'' (2019) and Bode Locke in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]'' (2020-).\n\n== Early Life ==\nScott was born and raised in [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]].<ref name=\"AZFamily.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.azfamily.com/archives/it-has-valley-connection/article_eb4d88d0-08ce-5bb2-ac0f-0424c7817539.html|title='It' has Valley connection|last=Reporter|first=Maria Hechanova|website=AZFamily|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/entertainment/movies/2020/03/23/jackson-robert-scott-arizona-born-actor-locke-key-netflix-stephen-kings-it/4939992002/|title=You might know this Arizona-born actor as Georgie in 'It.' Now he's in a new Netflix show|last=Ludden|first=Nicole|website=azcentral|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He is enrolled in his school's Mandarin Immersion Program, in which he learns to speak [[Mandarin Chinese]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Jackson Robert Scott at the \"IT\" premiere on FabulousTV|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8httfWqfcPE|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> He is also a [[Boy Scouts of America|boy scout]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Begj9RPFaDB/|title=Jackson Robert Scott\u2019s Instagram photo: \u201cHaving fun at the Cub Scout Pinewood Derby Race... A 65 year old tradition! \ud83c\udfce\ud83d\udea6\ud83c\udfc1 #cubscouts #cubscoutsofamerica #pinewoodderby\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bf4wO__FXYZ/|title=Jackson Robert Scott on Instagram: \u201cCrossed the bridge...I\u2019m now officially a Webelo! \ud83d\ude01\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8DT94DlzFD/|title=Jackson Robert Scott on Instagram: \u201cMy 5th Pinewood Derby Race! \ud83c\udfce\ud83c\udfc1Such a fun day with my Cub Scout/Arrow of Light troop! #cubscouts #pinewoodderby #boyscoutsofamerica\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nHe was a part of the CGTV acting program where he learned a lot of his acting techniques. While at the CGTV program, he worked with actors from [[Nickelodeon]] and [[Disney]], as well as [[Adrian R'Mante]], the founder of CGTV.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/celebrating-silver-screen-debut-cgtv-graduate/|title=Celebrating the Silver Screen Debut of a CGTV Graduate|last=R'Mante|date=2017-09-06|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> His favorite class was Improvisational Workshop.<ref name=\"Jackson Robert Scott Hits Prime Time TV\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/cgtv-alum-jackson-robert-scott-hits-prime-time-tv-hollywood/|title=Jackson Robert Scott Hits Prime Time TV|last=R'Mante|date=2016-12-29|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nHe was discovered by a top agency some time after his time with CGTV and began his start in auditioning and self-taping for top-tier television shows.<ref name=\"5 Year gets 15 agent callbacks and secures a costar role in Criminal Minds after CGTV\">{{Cite web|url=https://cgtv.la/criminal-minds-after-cgtv/|title=5 Year gets 15 agent callbacks|last=R'Mante|date=2016-07-27|website=CGTV|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nScott got his breakout role in 2015 on ''[[Criminal Minds]]'', a prime time American TV series. Scott was cast in [[Criminal_Minds_(season_11)|Season 11]]\u2019s fourth episode, titled \"Outlaw\", as Cole Vasquez. The episode aired on October 21, 2015.<ref name=\"Criminal Minds 11x04 IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=Outlaw|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt4920092/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> He also played a minor character in an episode of ''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]'' titled \"[[TEOTWAWKI_(Fear_the_Walking_Dead)|TEOTWAWKI]]\", playing the child version of the character Troy Otto.<ref name=\"Fear The Walking Dead 3x03 IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=TEOTWAWKI|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt6082752/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Scott was cast to play [[Georgie Denbrough]] in the [[It_(2017_film)|2017 film adaptation]] of [[Stephen King|Stephen King's]] novel [[It (novel)|''It'']].<ref name=\":0\" /> Georgie is a character that [[It (character)|Pennywise the Dancing Clown]] haunts at the start of the film. Scott has said that he did not feel intimidated or scared of [[Bill Skarsg\u00e5rd]], who played Pennywise, as Skarsg\u00e5rd was a nice person in real life.<ref name=\"Video Interview of Jackson at the premiere of IT in 2017\">{{Citation|title=\ud83c\udf6d Jackson Robert Scott co-stars with Bill Skarsg\u00e5rd (Pennywise) & describes him with & no makeup|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qmKLb1KczPI|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Scott attended the premiere for the film at [[Grauman's Chinese Theatre]].<ref name=\"Another Jackson Interview at the IT premiere\">{{Citation|title=Jackson Robert Scott (Georgie) - \"IT\" Premiere 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bkAhne1Xk6I|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> He reprised his role of Georgie in the sequel, ''[[It Chapter Two]]'', which was released on September 6, 2019.<ref name=\"IT: Chapter Two IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=It: Chapter Two|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt7349950/|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nScott was cast in the role of Troy for the short film [[Skin_(2018_short_film)|''Skin'']] (2018), directed by Guy Nattiv, which would go on to win the [[Academy Award for Best Live Action Short Film]] at the [[91st Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Skin Oscar Page\">{{Cite web|title=Skin: Short Film (Live Action) Oscar Nominees 2019|url=https://oscar.go.com/nominees/short-film-live-action/skin|website=oscar.go.com|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Skin Wins Oscar\">{{Citation|title=\"Skin\" wins Best Live Action Short Film|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x-fsRO3CbW8|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nContinuing in the horror genre, Scott played the title role of Miles Blume in the 2019 film [[The Prodigy (film)|''The Prodigy'']], directed by [[Nicholas_McCarthy_(director)|Nicholas McCarthy]]. This marked his first starring role in a feature film, and he co-starred alongside [[Taylor Schilling]].<ref name=\"Jackson cast in The Prodigy article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/jackson-robert-scott-horror-movie-taylor-schilling-nicholas-mccarthy-midnight-meat-train-1202308536/|title=Jackson Robert Scott Joins Orion\u2019s Horror Pic From Nicholas McCarthy|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|date=2018-03-02|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"The Prodigy Trailer\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/the-prodigy-trailer-taylor-schilling-jackson-robert-scott-1202529056/|title=\u2018The Prodigy\u2019 Trailer: Taylor Schilling Tries To Make Sense Of Her Young Son\u2019s Strange Behavior|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|date=2019-01-04|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n[[Andr\u00e9s Muschietti]] had recruited Scott to be a part of his one-hour series pilot of ''[[Locke & Key]]'' for [[Hulu]] as one of the leading young actors opposite [[Frances O'Connor]]. He played the part of Bode Locke, the youngest of the siblings.<ref name=\"Jackson Hulu L&K Pilot Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/locke-key-it-jackson-robert-scott-cast-hulu-pilot-1202157390/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019: Young \u2018It\u2019 Co-Star To Play Bode Locke In Hulu Pilot|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2017-08-29|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Hulu passed on the pilot and declined to order it to series.<ref name=\"Hulu passed over Locke & Key series Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/locke-key-pilot-dead-not-going-to-series-hulu-pauses-pilot-orders-shopped-1202354352/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019 Not Going To Series At Hulu As Streamer Pauses Pilot Orders|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2018-03-27|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> However, [[Netflix]] later redeveloped the [[Locke & Key (TV series)|series]] with a new cast, only keeping Scott as Bode from the Hulu cast.<ref name=\"Netflix orders Locke & Key to series Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/locke-key-drama-carlton-cuse-joe-hill-series-order-netflix-aron-eli-coleite-meredith-averill-1202433692/|title=\u2018Locke & Key\u2019 Drama From Carlton Cuse & Joe Hill Gets Series Order At Netflix, Aron Eli Coleite & Meredith Averill Join As EPs|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2018-07-25|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> The first season was released on Netflix on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/locke-key-gets-netflix-premiere-date-1259502|title='Locke & Key' Gets Netflix Premiere Date, Ending 9-Year Journey to Screen|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref> Scott stated in an interview for [[The Arizona Republic|AZCentral]] that Bode has been his favorite character to play, because he shared a lot of qualities with that character, such as his fun-loving personality and his love of bacon. The writers of the show met Jackson while filming so they could incorporate aspects from his real life personality into the character of Bode. Scott also said in the same interview that he grew very close to the other actors of ''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]'' while they were filming the show.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2018, Scott was cast in the role of Tate Millikin for the upcoming independent film ''Gossamer Folds,'' directed by Lisa Donato. He co-stars with [[Alexandra Grey]] and [[Shane West]]. The film is produced by [[Yeardley Smith]].<ref name=\"Gossamer Folds Annoucement Article\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/yeardley-smiths-paperclip-ltd-gossamer-folds-alexandra-grey-lisa-donato-lgbtq-diversity-inclusion-1202502237/|title=Yeardley Smith\u2019s Paperclip Ltd. Sets Transgender Drama \u2018Gossamer Folds\u2019 Starring \u2018Transparent\u2019s Alexandra Grey|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|last2=Ramos|first2=Dino-Ray|date=2018-11-15|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[It (2017 film)|It]]''\n|[[Georgie Denbrough]]\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Skin (2018 short film)|Skin]]''\n|Troy\n|Academy Award for Best Live Action Short Film\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Prodigy (film)|The Prodigy]]''\n|Miles Blume\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[It Chapter Two]]''\n|Georgie Denbrough\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''Gossamer Folds''\n|Tate Millikin\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''Rising''\n|Luke\n|Post-production, short film<ref name=\"Rising (2020) IMDB Page\">{{Citation|title=Rising (2020)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11093922/|access-date=2019-10-11}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Criminal Minds]]''\n|Cole Vasquez\n|Episode: \"Outlaw\"\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Fear the Walking Dead]]''\n|Young Troy Otto\n|Episode: \"[[TEOTWAWKI (Fear the Walking Dead)|TEOTWAWKI]]\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Locke & Key (TV series)|Locke & Key]]''\n|Bode Locke\n|Main role\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [[imdbname:7669135|Jackson Robert Scott]] on [[IMDb]]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/jacksonrobertscottofficial/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Instagram]]\n*[https://twitter.com/jacksonrscottit/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Twitter]]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/JacksonRobertScottOfficial/ Jackson Robert Scott] on [[Facebook]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scott, Jackson Robert}}\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:2008 births]]\n[[Category:People from